# Python Code Conventions

When editing Python files in `python/`:

## Package Management
- Prefer `uv` over `pip` when available
- `uv sync` to install deps, `uv run pytest` to test
- Dependencies go in `requirements.in` (compiled to `requirements.txt`)

## Style
- Follow PEP 8
- Type hints on all public function signatures
- Docstrings on public functions and classes (Google style)

## Testing
- Tests in `python/tests/` using pytest
- Run: `uv run pytest python/tests/ -v`
- Use `pytest.mark.parametrize` for data-driven tests

## Key Modules
- `python/tui/` — Terminal UI (Textual framework)
- `python/bindings/` — Cython bindings to C++ core
- `python/tools/` — Developer tooling (MLX review, log summarizer, scorecard)
- `python/tests/` — Test suite

## Security
- Never hardcode credentials or API keys
- Use environment variables or config files for sensitive values
